# EasyTrading

Multi-DEX trading client for .NET (HyperLiquid + Aster + dYdX v4). See `AGENTS.md` for full guidance.

## Core rules

- `decimal` for all money values; never `double` / `float`
- `Async` suffix on every async method; `CancellationToken ct = default` last parameter
- Methods grouped by entity: `Orders`, `Positions`, `Markets`, `Trades`, `Account`, `Transfers`, `Streams`, plus HL-only `Vaults` / `Staking` / `Builder`
- WebSocket streams use `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` with `await foreach`
- Check `client.Capabilities.HasFlag(ExchangeCapabilities.X)` before calling optional features
- Typed exceptions: `RateLimitException`, `InsufficientFundsException`, `InvalidOrderException`, `AuthenticationException`, `SigningException`
- `from` / `to` for time-range parameters

## HyperLiquid specifics

- Prefer agent wallets to the master private key — call `IAccount.ApproveAgentAsync(...)` once, then use the agent's key for trading
- Builder fees / rebates are managed via `IBuilder` and applied automatically by `EasyTrading.Broker`
- Network: `HyperLiquidNetwork.Mainnet` or `.Testnet`

## DI registration

```csharp
services.AddEasyTrading()
        .AddHyperLiquid(o =>
        {
            o.Network     = HyperLiquidNetwork.Mainnet;
            o.Credentials = new HyperLiquidCredentials("0xMaster", privKey, agentName: "my-bot");
        });
```

Inject `IHyperLiquidExchange` (HL-specific surface) or `IExchangeClient` (cross-DEX).

## Common operations

```csharp
// Market data
var mids = await ex.Markets.GetAllMidsAsync(ct);
var book = await ex.Markets.GetOrderBookAsync("BTC", depth: 10, ct);

// Trading
await ex.Orders.PlaceLimitAsync("BTC", OrderSide.Buy, price: 60_000m, size: 0.01m, tif: TimeInForce.Alo, ct: ct);
await ex.Positions.SetLeverageAsync("BTC", 10, MarginMode.Cross, ct);
await ex.Positions.CloseAsync("BTC", ct);

// Streams
await foreach (var fill in ex.Streams.MyFillsAsync(ct))
    Console.WriteLine($"{fill.Symbol} {fill.Side} {fill.Size} @ {fill.Price}");
```

## Phase awareness

Phase 1 (current): scaffolding — all methods throw `NotImplementedException`. Real implementations land in Phase 2+. Don't worry if calls fail in test code — that's expected for the current snapshot. See `CHANGELOG.md`.
